        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Saller Lewin &#38; Co.<lb/>
                Wholesale<lb/>
                Boot &#38; Shoe Manufacturers<lb/>
                No. 313 Arch Street.<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia Sept. 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1885<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>The Board of Delegates of<lb/> the N.A.H.C. as p&#91;e&#93;r enclosed circular<lb/> have asked that Sunday Oct. 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> be<lb/> designated as a general day for Memorial<lb/> services throughout the U.S. in memory<lb/> of Sir Moses Montefiore. As representa&#45;<lb/>tives of Philada. on the B. of D. we<lb/> submit the matter to you to be<lb/> presented to the Jewish Ministers<lb/> of this City for further consideration.<lb/> Will you kindly advise us what<lb/> action they take in the matter&#91;.&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>Truly Yours<lb/>
                Philip Lewin<lb/>
                W<hi rend="sup">m</hi> B Hackenburg<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Gentlemen<lb/></p>
            <p>At a meeting held&#94; last evening at the residence<lb/> of Dr M. Jastrow&#44; your communication was<lb/> made the subject of discussion. The Ministers<lb/>  agreed that in as much as our respective Congre&#45;<lb/>gations&#8212;with a single unavoidable exception&#44; have<lb/> already held memorial services in honor of the<lb/> lamented Sir Moses Montefiore&#44; it would be<lb/> inexpedient to have  a repetition thereof jointly&#44;<lb/> at the time stated by the Board of Delegates that you represent.<lb/> With sentiments of personal regards&#44; I subscribe<lb/> myself<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly<lb/>
                S Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Sep 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1885<lb/>
                Messrs Philip Lewin &#38; Wm B. Hackenburg<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Union of American Hebrew Congregations.<lb/>
                Board of Delegates in Civil and Religious Rights.<lb/></p>
            <p>New York&#44; July 30&#44; 1885.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>At a meeting of the Board&#44; held this day&#44; to<lb/> take appropriate action upon the death of SIR MOSES<lb/> MONTEFIORE&#44; the following recommendations were<lb/> adopted&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>1.That during the thirty days following the funeral&#44; <lb/> special prayers be offered in the Synagogues&#44; Temples&#44; <lb/> and Charitable Institutions.<lb/></p>
            <p>2. That arrangements be made for a Memorial Ser&#45;<lb/>vice in each city&#44; to be held at the same time through&#45;<lb/>out the United States&#59; and Sunday&#44; October 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#44; is<lb/> suggested as a suitable day.<lb/></p>
            <p>3. That the benevolent work and institutions dear to<lb/> SIR MOSES MONTEFIORE&#44; or founded in his name&#44; be<lb/> accorded renewed sympathy and support.<lb/></p>
            <p>It becomes my duty to communicate this action and<lb/> to ask your reply&#44; indicating whether a memorial<lb/> service will be held on the day suggested.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly&#44;<lb/>
                M.S. ISAACS&#44; Chairman&#44;<lb/>
                115 BROADWAY&#44; N.Y.<lb/></p>
            </body>
